HEADWORD: Familist
<hw>Fam"i*list</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Family</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>One of a fanatical
Antinomian sect originating in Holland, and existing in England about
1580, called the <membof>Family of Love</membof>, who held that religion
consists wholly in love.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

